commit_message:
Implement permission changes during rsync

In order to ensure that the files and directories
that are gathered for logs are readable for the
rename and gzip processes, we ensure that the
permissions and ownership are set during the copy
handled by rsync.

The previous method resulted in the files being
copied, but some files not being writable when
executing mv/gzip. This was noticed in the
os_neutron role where the calico job was failing
due to permissions issues for the felix config
files in the container /etc directory.

Change-Id: I7b84e0db25f44842a88315cd413ac39f75f9f8b9

commit_message:
Remove main_db flavor compatibility

This removes the no-longer-used compatibility with flavors being either
in the main or api databases.

commit_message:
Fix bugs of redirect url

Horizon has some changes as bellow about security group and keypairs.
Sahara-dashboard should sync the location of resource with horizon.

* Move Security Groups into its own panel
	https://review.openstack.org/#/c/427882/
* Make Key Pairs tab a panel under Compute:
	 https://review.openstack.org/#/c/408247/

Change-Id: I705e2feff090acd1d17e58b3d77c185fd0006c19
(cherry picked from commit 0011eb6130193104b17b0cfcdc149ceff790ddc6)

commit_message:
Drop token-flush cronjob

We now only support fernet tokens, for which token flushing is no longer
needed, see [1]. So we drop the corresponding cron job and the
attributes to configure it. This also gets rid of the error messages
which it is currently producing.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/security-guide/identity/tokens.html#fernet-tokens

Change-Id: Ia5fe5f5d0c98ca0a77f03478edfe1777e0a89612
(cherry picked from commit 275c12c3a614df47feac20bb853b55d393b24556)

commit_message:
Assume neutron port_binding extensions enabled

No recent neutron deployment should ever have the port_binding extension
missing in its list.

It appears like this has been the case since this commit in Liberty:
61121c5f2af27e31092db7ac6947f796198410a8

It causing lots of confusion around when an admin_client should be used,
among other things, so lets remove this needless complexity.

Co-Authored-By: Augustina Ragwitz <auggy@cpan.org>
Change-Id: I5fa73fa0610b23ef231952b2035a284819186a7c
Related-Bug: 1608601

commit_message:
tasks: container_create: Retry if sysctl-container service failed to start

This aims to workaround an issue on openSUSE where the service may fail
to start with the following error:

sysctl-container.service: Failed at step CGROUP spawning /sbin/sysctl: No such device

Related-Bug: #1712741
Link: https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1055426
Change-Id: If66f1f9d0f51173890004b65c332f14fc878fb18

commit_message:
DNM Test default executor_thread_pool_size

It seems stable jobs are not giving max connection
exceeded error. Check if reverting to default works
on master.

Change-Id: Idbc5538f12348c49d6be9e9251b33aead36e6dc2

Thanks Richard Theis. 
I trid with varies of filter format as following. Only a filter with ['fixed_ips']='ip_address=x.x.x.x' or ['fixed_ips']='subnet_id=xxxx' works. It seems we cannot support the option alignment as used on other port commands.

        # filters['subnet_id'] = '11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9'
        # curl is ports?subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9
        # Take no effect, all ports returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = {'subnet_id': '11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9'}
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=%7B%27subnet_id%27%3A+%2711668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%27%7D
        # We got exception:
        # HttpException: Invalid input for operation: 'subnet_id' is not of the form <key>=[value].

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = [{'subnet_id': '11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9'}]
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=%5B%7B%27subnet_id%27%3A+%2711668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%27%7D%5D
        # We got exception:
        # HttpException: Invalid input for operation: 'subnet_id' is not of the form <key>=[value].

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "{'subnet_id': '11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9'}"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=%7B%27subnet_id%27%3A+%2711668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%27%7D
        # We got exception:
        # HttpException: Invalid input for operation: '{'subnet_id': '11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9'}' is not of the form <key>=[value].

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9
        # it does work! Only the ports with givin subnet_id returned.

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9,ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%2Cip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9&ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%26ip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9 ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9+ip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9=ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%3Dip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "subnet_id=11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9?ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=subnet_id%3D11668518-7bd6-49ce-b384-45f432e985b9%3Fip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # it does work!

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address='10.0.0.1'"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D%2710.0.0.1%27
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address=10.0.0.1"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D10.0.0.1
        # it does work!

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address='10.0.0.1'"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D%2710.0.0.1%27
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "[ip_address=10.0.0.1]"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=%5Bip_address%3D10.0.0.1%5D
        # Take no effect

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address=10.0.0.1|ip_address=10.0.0.2"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D10.0.0.1%7Cip_address%3D10.0.0.2
        # Take no effect

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address=[10.0.0.1]"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D%5B10.0.0.1%5D
        # No entries returned

        # filters['fixed_ips'] = "ip_address=10.0.0.1,10.0.0.2"
        # curl is ports?fixed_ips=ip_address%3D10.0.0.1%2C10.0.0.2
        # No entries returned'}, {'account_id': 19644, 'date': '2016-11-13 03:34:07.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2016-11-13 04:43:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

commit_message:
Fix usage of --kubelet-preferred-address arg for apiserver

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/439906/ fixed it only for
tls based cluster, we need kubectl exec/log to work with
tls-disabled clusters as well.

Change-Id: Iae2d4bc9af7fc55ab0ce2db97c6b7cf61479a2ff
Closes-Bug: #1668337
(cherry picked from commit 8e36613965619c480f57f069bb1d46ecd4c626d7)

result in multiple processes save same DB entry concurrently.

Close-Bug: #1711324
'}]
commit_message:
Deal with db_exc.DBDuplicate of conductor startup

we have enable multiple workers of magnum-conductor that
result in multiple processes save same DB entry concurrently.

This patch logs warning message instead of raising exception

Change-Id: I548d50bed5d80e96042f88039e880075e1bffc53
Close-Bug: #1711324

commit_message:
Make Ansible env variables configurable

Some env variables set for the ansible-playbook execution were
hardcoded; this change configures them as a default workflow
input so they can be overridden from the called (tripleo templates).

Also adds to the list /var/log/mistral as default location
for the ceph-install workflow logging.

Change-Id: Ibf748c5ee579e4c84785b6ef7674ee32fc3573e5

commit_message:
Remove TENANT_NAME from /etc/sysconfig/heat-params

1. It will fail to create cluster if there is chinese in tenant name
2. TENANT_NAME is unnecessary after changing to trustee

this patch is for k8s_fedora_atomic and k8s_fedora_ironic

Change-Id: Ie072f183110ae95861fb3694a913a3a4526549fb
Close-Bug: #1711308
(cherry picked from commit 048400bd4bbbf3bdf80f8b391712c5bc1e9dde79)

commit_message:
Remove usage of parameter enforce_type

Oslo.config deprecated parameter enforce_type and change its default
value to True in Ifa552de0a994e40388cbc9f7dbaa55700ca276b0. Remove the
usage of it to avoid DeprecationWarning: "Using the 'enforce_type'
argument is deprecated in version '4.0' and will be removed in version
'5.0': The argument enforce_type has changed its default value to True
and then will be removed completely."

Change-Id: Ibfb2ccddb5fb80d1ae4f9f39e42305646bb2da12

commit_message:
Fix KeyError exception

During the strategy sync process,
if goal_id can't be found in the goals table,
will throw a KeyError exception.

Change-Id: I62800ac5c69f4f5c7820908f2e777094a51a5541
Closes-Bug: #1711086

commit_message:
Using threading executor for messaging listener,

not specifying a default listener causes a blocking listener to be used
which interupts the 'listener.start()' call if the messaging server is
not reachable.

Using threading gives a chance for other reachable servers, which are
down in the list, to start.

Closes bug: 1657329

Change-Id: Id8bd0820146d8967e0b20b2f6363d00cab04a125

commit_message:
Update docs/tooling for Queens

In the upgrade tooling and the docs references we use
the series name in a few places. This updates them all
for development in the Queens cycle.

In the docs there are many references to Ocata manuals
which are left alone as the upstream Pike docs have not
been published yet.

Change-Id: Ice2169bd40f5712dd9ec9a9eb946fe0244f32294

Pin ARA for Pike

To ensure that ARA continues to work for the lifetime
of Pike, we pin it to the current version.

commit_message:
Compile SELinux module via async

This patch adjusts the SELinux rule compile task to run with async.
Some CI jobs are CPU-bound and this compile step can take 30-45
seconds to complete on slower machines.

Change-Id: Ia20b8cc00ad3bad6d6ccf9cd995d0ef24f2090a0
(cherry picked from commit 79e5e571de875cdc00047b3396ae39ea0feff072)

commit_message:
base: add support for fetching APT keys from files

For RPM distros we use GPG keys as URLs because rpm can handle it.

For Debian based distros we fetch GPG keys from ubuntu keyserver. But it
does not work with OBS repositories where key is provided as file in
repo.

This change adds support for fetching GPG keys for APT use.

Change-Id: I6b205a2bb61207d1549222ba5501536b2743df77

commit_message:
Replaces yaml.load() with yaml.safe_load()

Yaml.load() return Python object may be dangerous if you receive
a YAML document from an untrusted source such as the Internet.
The function yaml.safe_load() limits this ability to simple
Python objects like integers or lists.

Reference:
https://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html

Change-Id: I021bd09d3bbc6d4b9c8965c59c7f4ec4895f8b8b

commit_message:
Separate greenfield and upgrade tests

In order to independently test a greenfield deploy
and an upgrade, with the upgrade's initial deploy
using the previous stable branch role, we seperate
the two tests.

This makes it a more accurate test without having
to do funky workarounds in the role required to
cater for two versions of galera.

Depends-On: Ic881bf3acf6fb6daf71611c26322f02fb8b0b9be
Depends-On: I5c88b2019c01b44193a5d0df9299ecce6de52f01
Depends-On: I8b09c2520c84bb43353b4c56bac157259f71b041
Needed-By: Ife56dc9a4eb32d86c5f43544e67569f60ce5976c
Change-Id: I0c74e511cec01ed51101b873784c4a90a7302da6
(cherry picked from commit 0227dbe40dfd4d21a8a92ec038a608efab5ebe18)

WIP: Add scenario007-multinode-container CI templates for OVN containers

This patch is for testing this scenario. Once all the tests passes,
the scenario007 files would be moved into this patch -
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/468860/

Specify the start count to 0 for the update step loop

Force the count start to 0 to ensure that the
update step loop will start to 0 and execute the
update step0

commit_message:
Delete instance allocations when the instance is deleted

In a deployment that still has Ocata computes, the resource
tracker will delete the allocations for an instance when it
is deleted, but in an all-Pike+ computes deployment, the
allocations will only be removed for a deleted instance
during the update_available_resource periodic task.

The capacity on the node should be freed as soon as the
instance is deleted, like when we shelve offload an
instance, so this does that.

The ServerMovingTests functional tests were glossing over
this by forcing the run of the update_available_resource
periodic task code after the instance was deleted but
before checking the allocations were gone from Placement.
So this change removes that part of the tests to show
this fixes the problem.

Change-Id: I0f57b4ba8e4c3931b70bd737de5b7c8ae47f033d
Closes-Bug: #1712684

commit_message:
workload balance base on cpu or ram util

By the input parameter "metrics", it makes decision to migrate a VM
base on cpu or memory utilization.

Change-Id: I35cce3495c8dacad64ea6c6ee71082a85e9e0a83
(cherry picked from commit 5c86a54d20f5034c06073617446e0b0bc2e1436d)

commit_message:
Remove watcher_tempest_plugin

In accordance with Queens global goal[1], this patch set
removes watcher tempest plugin from watcher repository since
it is stored as independent repository[2]. Jenkins job
gate-watcher-dsvm-multinode-ubuntu-xenial-nv has been modified,
it uses watcher-tempest-plugin repo now.

[1]: https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/queens/split-tempest-plugins.html
[2]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/watcher-tempest-plugin/

Change-Id: I4d1207fbd73ee2519a6d40342f5fd3c5d3ee8bc7

commit_message:
Remove pbr warnerrors

This change removes the now unused "warnerrors" setting,
which is replaced by "warning-is-error" in sphinx
releases >= 1.5 [1].

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-March/113085.html

Change-Id: I32f078169668be08737e47cd15edbdfba42904dc
(cherry picked from commit f76a628d1fc330d5934e463a2bbb262f30b6439b)

commit_message:
Added Tempest API client methods and Tempest tests for sessions and deployments

Added tests for following scenarios:
    * deploy session
    * list all deployments
    * list deployments (in a specific environment)
    * list a specific deployment's statuses

Added application_catalog_client methods for following functionality:
    * list all deployments
    * list deployments (in a specific environment)
    * list a specific deployment's statuses

Change-Id: I0ac1b2a6216fd1794ba06ee0b26e6c2c90118526

commit_message:
Deal with db_exc.DBDuplicate of conductor startup

we have enable multiple workers of magnum-conductor that
result in multiple processes save same DB entry concurrently.

This patch logs warning message instead of raising exception

Change-Id: I548d50bed5d80e96042f88039e880075e1bffc53
Close-Bug: #1711324

import whereto program

whereto is a program for testing Apache redirect rules. We intend to
use it in the openstack-manuals CI jobs.

commit_message:
add section for tls

If we do not configure section keystone_auth, then the magnum
will post error when tls_disabled is false. So we should add
it here.

There were some questions in IRC for this review about where the Ceph package is coming from and why packages are being installed at all. Details on how scenario001 was changed, which answers some of these questions, are in the https://review.openstack.org/#/c/479288 under my comments at Aug 4 10:03 PM, Aug 6 6:42 PM, and Aug 6 9:55 PM. To summarize:

1. Why do you need ceph packages on the overcloud nodes if Ceph is running in containers?

The container host to runs 'ceph --version' [1]. If the package isn't there, then this command fails. 

2. Why does tripleo's ceph-ansible integration install the packages and are you using ceph.com?

It installs no packages unless you use deployed servers. We don't use ceph.com packages. As per the docs [2], in the deployed-server scenario: "servers will need to already have the appropriately enabled yum repositories" but "packages will be installed on the servers during the Overcloud deployment". puppet-nova installs nova packages in this scenario, so why shouldn't ceph-ansible? So, we need ceph-ansible to install the Ceph packages, but not set up the repositories. The repository is already set to the centos storage sig by CI [3]. So the change to scenario001 was to tell ceph-ansible to install packages (by dropping --skip-tags package-install,with_pkg). 

3. Why do we install these extra packages including EPEL?

We may not need them so we'll try to get rid of them by overriding the list of extra packages ceph-ansible installs with an empty one as per patchset 4 [4]. If we find a package missing, e.g. perhaps we need hdparm, then we can add it back. I think doing so is consistent with the needs of deployed-servers [2] and then we should document Ceph installs for the deployed-servers scenario. 

[1] https://github.com/ceph/ceph-ansible/blob/9da848abaca0798fa627dcb09aefed6636da76ea/roles/ceph-common/tasks/main.yml#L101-L105
[2] http://tripleo.org/advanced_deployment/deployed_server.html#package-repositories
[3] https://github.com/openstack-infra/tripleo-ci/blob/master/scripts/tripleo.sh#L306-L312
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/496806/1..4/ci/environments/scenario001-multinode-containers.yaml'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-08-23 20:36:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

commit_message:
Do not install additional CentOS packages via ceph-ansible

EPEL is required by the Ceph RPM repo maintained at ceph.com but
not by the CentOS SIG repo. The other packages should be already
installed in the infra image.

This change overrides the list of required packages in ceph-ansible
so that it does not install epel-release nor additional unneeded
packages [1].

1. https://github.com/ceph/ceph-ansible/blob/master/group_vars/all.yml.sample#L67

Change-Id: I7b6d2794ebfc0df5b3d5ad9de1d1d55740a38ae0
Closes-Bug: #1712599

Closes-Bug: #1668337

commit_message:
Drop token-flush cronjob

We now only support fernet tokens, for which token flushing is no longer
needed, see [1]. So we drop the corresponding cron job and the
attributes to configure it. This also gets rid of the error messages
which it is currently producing.

commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Change job type for 3nodes job to move to oooq runner""

We now have the 3nodes patches all merged, so it is safe to revert this
revert.

This reverts commit 06c161d0d7020dbed097c945e0b378995e087654.

commit_message:
Remove TENANT_NAME from /etc/sysconfig/heat-params

1. It will fail to create cluster if there is chinese in tenant name
2. TENANT_NAME is unnecessary after changing to trustee

this patch is for k8s_fedora_atomic and k8s_fedora_ironic

Change-Id: Ie072f183110ae95861fb3694a913a3a4526549fb
Close-Bug: #1711308

commit_message:
ensure tripleo scenario003 checks trigger on changes

A follow up patch to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/496830/
This patch should ensure that when changes are made to
tripleo-quickstart-extras or openstack-infra the right check
is made.

Checks:
 - tqe/roles
 - tripleo-ci/toci-quickstart/config|playbooks)
 - tripoleo-ci/toci_.* scripts

Change-Id: I6ad1bf4761cc4252767db30822835301fa78975f

commit_message:
Adjust the action state judgment logic

Only when True is returned, the action state is set to SUCCEEDED
some actions(such as migrate) will return None if exception raised

Change-Id: I52e7a1ffb68f54594f2b00d9843e8e0a4c985667
(cherry picked from commit 965af1b6fd4c52627bfb1d772543cb2410b57537)

commit_message:
Improve the Cinder docs

* Remove redundant info, e.g. 'kolla can deploy the cinder services'

* List the available backends Kolla supports

* The bug wrt to lvm with multiple control nodes is open rather than
  'WontFix', update the note to reflect this.

* Document how to configure the NFS backend

Change-Id: I1621efa35a329676ecaf309d60f578d33d8aa0d4

subject: Add all teams
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 612, 'name': 'Tom Fifield', 'email': 'tom@openstack.org', 'username': 'fifieldt'}, {'_account_id': 7272, 'name': 'Matt Van Winkle', 'email': 'mvanwinkle@salesforce.com', 'username': 'mvanwink'}, {'_account_id': 12651, 'name': 'Shamail Tahir', 'email': 'ItzShamail@gmail.com', 'username': 'shamail'}, {'_account_id': 14091, 'name': 'Yih Leong Sun', 'email': 'yihleong@gmail.com', 'username': 'yihleongsun'}, {'_account_id': 16157, 'name': 'Ken Johnston', 'email': 'kenny@kencjohnston.com', 'username': 'kencjohnston'}, {'_account_id': 17505, 'name': 'Saverio Proto', 'email': 'saverio.proto@switch.ch', 'username': 'zioproto'}]

[{'account_id': 17556, 'date': '2017-02-22 04:48:28.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-02-22 04:50:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-governance-uc-docs-ubuntu-xenial http://docs-draft.openstack.org/57/436757/1/check/gate-governance-uc-docs-ubuntu-xenial/a2c2ce7//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 2m 17s'}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2017-02-22 07:28:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Do these teams meet the standard required by the user committee?

For example, the ops tags team has not met in months.

"Massively Distributed Clouds" has a defined end-point ("delivering an OpenStack architecture that can natively cooperate with other instances, giving the illusion of a global cloud"), so it would probably be classed as a working group rather than a Team.

I note that there is no written process for adding WGS/Teams to this repo at current. I'd recommend the UC take the opportunity of having the new repository to meet and create that process for formally adding teams and working groups.

This should also help with the confusion surrounding overlap between LCOO/LDT/MDC/Public Clouds'}, {'account_id': 12651, 'date': '2017-02-22 07:34:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

(1 comment)

Hi Tom, would it be okay to merge this to gain parity between this page and the teams listed on the UC wiki page[1] for now and then we can re-evaluate each team/WG over the next few weeks to see if they meet the standard?

[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Governance/Foundation/UserCommittee'}, {'account_id': 612, 'date': '2017-02-22 07:42:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hi Shamail,

I'd strongly recommend the UC makes a process first.

Only stuff that's rock solid should live in a governance repository (see TC as an example here), and there are clear issues with the quality of some teams and working groups listed on the wiki.

It's going to take some time to resolve, but I think you'll get a much better response by encouraging improvement to reach a certain quality level prior to addition on an official basis. The alternative being proposed is based on threat-of-removal, which isn't as strong a motivating factor given the UC's relatively new basis as a governance body."}, {'account_id': 12651, 'date': '2017-02-22 07:50:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

+1 Tom, based on our conversation in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/436752/1, I agree with defining the process/standards first.'}, {'account_id': 16157, 'date': '2017-02-22 21:56:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Great point Tom about using the opportunity to define a process.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-08-02 15:13:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

commit_message:
Add stubs for new ovsdbapp API functions

Neutron doesn't use these methods, but they will be added to
ovsdbapp 1.0, and being abstractmethods, would cause an error. The
methods are added in I664add660ce0ec3b0da23325ad38580d850e1f29 and
I9352ffe0f245c579fd766ecd00e8ca512f806798.

Change-Id: Ibfdea4890f7d01ddd38872db40a9829d6b6bdf90

commit_message:
Make get-occ-config.sh support custom roles

Updates the get-occ-config.sh script used with the deployed-server
environment to support custom roles. Any custom role name, and a
corresponding set of hosts (ip addresses or hostnames) can now be passed
to the script and it will query for the proper nested stack uuid's and
configure os-collect-config appropriately on the respective nodes.

Closes-Bug: #1712436

Change-Id: I8fc39e6d18cd70ff881e2a284234b26261018d67
(cherry picked from commit 64e44e8626e394a8ec41c798769893c0629958a3)

commit_message:
Replace map(lambda...) with comprehensions

List comprehensions and generator expressions are considered to be more
Pythonic (and usually more readable) than map with lambda.
This patch replaces four usages of map(lambda...) with the appropriate
list comprehension or generator expression.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I1ef13325740b063ab33d9559206a6a014bc238e1
